# Force LF in the working tree on every platform. Every tracked file is
# text (.capa, .md, .toml, .lock, .py, LICENSE, .asc, .yml), so a
# blanket eol=lf keeps output byte-identical across operating systems,
# which is what the "byte-identical on both backends" claim needs.
* text=auto eol=lf

# NOTHING is export-ignored. tools/ used to be, on the reasoning that it
# holds developer helpers rather than application code, but that made the
# release tarball contradict its own README: the documented build step is
# `python tools/nest_vendor.py`, without which `--check-capabilities`
# fails closed on a layout question, and the tarball did not carry the
# script. A verification step that only the development tree can run is
# not a verification step, so tools/ ships.
